    "sections": {
      "PURPOSE": "3/2CR requires Soldiers to group and zero their individual weapon systems in preparation to qualify on individual weapon systems and prepare for future combat operations.",
      "MISSION": "3/2CR conducts Group/Zero and Qualification Range IOT qualify on individual weapon systems and prepare for future combat operations.",
      "END STATE": "All firers complete Table VI (Qualification) IAW with Appendix E, TC 3-20.40\nConcept of the Operation: This OPN will be conducted in III Phases:\nPhase I (Planning & Prep): Begins with identifying personnel to be trained and provide range support and ends when Range Support personnel SP to Range 123 NLT 020700OCT23.",
      "KEY TASKS": "100% accountability of MWE, police call range, range cleared, ammo pickup, and safe movement back to RB.\nService & Support: Class I: M-M-M\nClass V: 100,000 Rounds 5.56MM Loose (AB57), 30,000 5.56 MM Linked (AB73)\n30 Rounds for Grouping and Zeroing per Firer\n40 Rounds AB57 Per Firer/Iteration\n100 Rounds AB73 Per Firer/Iteration\nMedical Support: PLT Medics Ammo DO – 020800OCT23/Ammo PU – 051430OCT23",
      "EXECUTION": "): Begins when range support personnel SP to Range 123 and ends when training is complete NLT 051500OCT23.",
      "COMMAND AND SIGNAL": "PACE Plan\nP: 163 (TSM)\nA: 163 (SINGARS)\nC: ATAK (HNC) E: Signal\nCourse of Fire: IAW TC 3-20.40\nUniform: Slick during G&Z and IAW Dragoon Standard during Qual\n23AUG23\n27SEP23\n28SEP23\n02-05OCT23\nTBD\n1. Plan the Training\n2. Train/Certify Leader\n3. Recon Training Site\n4. Issue the OPORD\n5. Rehearsal\n6. Exec. the Training\n7. Conduct an AAR\n8. Retrain/Retry\n29SEP23\n11OCT23\n26SEP23\nN\nPersonnel Required: 1x OIC, 1x RSO, 2x Gate Guard, 5x Safeties, 1x Medic, 2x MEV Crew, 1x Ammo NCO, 2x Ammo Detail, Fire Detail x2\nEquipment Required: Range Box, Engineer Tape, 2x DOS CL I, A8 Targetry, 1x MEV, 10x Barriers\nTimeline: 02-04OCT23\n0530 – FF\n0600 – Arms Room Draw\n0700 – Range Support SP\n0730 – Range Support RP/Occupy\n0800 – Troops Arrive/Ammo Drop\n0845 – Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1800 – Range Dry\n2000 – Night Safety Brief\n2030 – Ammo Draw\n2100 – Range Wet\n2300 – Range Dry\nRG123 M4/M249 Qualification CONOP\nTimeline 05OCT23\n0800 - Troops Arrives\n0845– Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1400 – Range Dry\n1430 – Ammo Pick-up\nNLT 1500 – Range Clear\nRange 123\nGrid: 32U QA 10024 05790\nSix Lanes\nFour reserved for qualification and two reserved for G&Z\nPriority of fire IAW with posted Regimental Schedule\nSquadrons are responsible for providing their own transportation and coaches\nParking\nTower/Ammo\nUnit Priority RG 123\nRG 123 Troops to Task"
    },
